If it's non-native table with custom storage handler, it's right to throw exception. But if it's native table with custom serde, we need not to verify serde of the table. Furthermore, in checkValidity() method,
{code}
if (0 == getCols().size()) throw new HiveException();
{code}
Is not needed except creating a table or partition. [~ashutoshc], can I reopen this issue?
